items.Video_Title: STOP Ruining Your Boots With Saddle Soap | How to Clean and Condition Leather Boots The Right Way!
items.Video_Description: My father-in-law has done it. My friends have done it... They grab a big ole dollop of saddle soap, rub it all over their boots, and treat it like shoe polish. The problem is that saddle soap is an astringent. It has lye and other acids that will actually hurt your leather over time if you don't completely remove the saddle soap after application. In this video, I'll show you how to properly apply saddle soap and how to condition and protect your leather boots so they can stand up to the elements, work, and play.
